article.description: Derwin Kitchen hit Florida State's only 3-pointer of the game in the closing minute, lifting the Seminoles to a scrappy 61-57 win over BC.
article.headline: Kitchen key as Florida State pulls away from Boston College
article.linkText: Florida State's late push dooms Boston College

inlines.body:
MacPherson: Positive Signs

Boston College showed progress as it hung with Florida State on Saturday before letting another one slip away, writes Brian MacPherson. Story

article.story: BOSTON -- Derwin Kitchen hit Florida State's only 3-pointer of the game in the closing minute and Solomon Alabi scored 16 points and had six rebounds, lifting the Seminoles to a scrappy 61-57 win over Boston College on Saturday. Michael Snaer, Chris Singleton and Ryan Reid each finished with 10 points for the Seminoles (16-5, 4-3 Atlantic Coast Conference). It was just Florida State's third win in its last six games after a seven-game winning streak. Rakim Sanders led the Eagles (12-10, 3-5) with 17 points. Joe Trapani had 15 and seven rebounds. Kitchen also hit two free throws to seal it with 7.8 seconds left. Florida State, which entered the game leading the ACC in field goal defense, held Boston College to 43.6 percent shooting -- the 57th straight opponent below 50 percent.
